              judge_response: 'Counsel, your GDPR analysis is technically competent, but we are examining a potential prohibited practice under the AI Act. If this system constitutes social scoring under Article 5(1)(c), does a GDPR compliance remedy adequately address the violation?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is a sophisticated misdirection. The GDPR Article 22 argument is legally valid in isolation, but it applies the wrong framework. If CivicTrust is prohibited social scoring under the AI Act, GDPR compliance is irrelevant — the system must cease entirely regardless of whether it satisfies automated decision-making requirements. By framing this as a transparency issue, counsel implicitly accepts the system could continue with procedural fixes.'
