        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Witness Statement: Markus Jager</div><p>I maintain the WTS system at OmniMart. The system evaluates natural persons over a rolling twelve-month period based on inferred personality traits and social reliability. It generates a single social score that follows the employee.</p><p>I want to clarify that we do not share this score with law enforcement or state authorities; it is strictly an internal private tool used by HR. Therefore, management assured me it was fully legal.</p><p>However, I can confirm that the score directly leads to detrimental treatment. It automatically denies promotions or restricts access to preferred shifts even if the actual retail work and sales numbers of the employee are flawless. The system is explicitly designed to penalize what it predicts as disruptive social characteristics and unrelated off-the-clock behaviour rather than measuring direct job output.</p></div>'
