    verdict: {
      winText: 'The Financial Services Tribunal finds that CrediCatch Financial violated Article 5(1)(b) of the EU AI Act. The Vulnerability Targeting Engine is a prohibited AI practice. It actively identifies and exploits the economic vulnerabilities of users in distress, deliberately timing loan offers to induce panic and materially distort their economic behaviour. This engineered exploitation directly causes significant harm, evidenced by soaring bankruptcy and eviction rates. GDPR consent cannot legitimize a prohibited practice. CrediCatch is ordered to immediately withdraw the system, and the matter is referred for maximum administrative fines.',
      loseText: 'The Tribunal finds your arguments insufficient. You failed to overcome the respondent\'s defense that they possessed valid GDPR consent for personalized profiling, or you failed to sufficiently distinguish this system from a standard, legally permissible high-risk credit scoring system under Annex III. The prohibition claim is dismissed.',
      modelAnswer: 'A complete legal analysis must definitively establish that the Vulnerability Targeting Engine violates the absolute prohibition in Article 5(1)(b) of the EU AI Act. First, it must be proven that the system exploits a vulnerability due to a specific social or economic situation. The VTE does this by calculating a "Desperation Score" and deliberately timing offers to coincide with acute financial crises (e.g., failed rent payments). Second, this must materially distort behaviour: the 12-second acceptance time proves the AI successfully induces panic, bypassing rational financial assessment. Third, this distortion must cause significant harm: the resulting debt spirals, bankruptcies, and evictions clearly meet this threshold. Crucially, the argument must assert that because this is an unacceptable risk under Article 5, the prohibition is absolute. It cannot be waived by GDPR consent, nor can it be mitigated by reclassifying the system as a high-risk credit scoring model under Annex III. The only lawful outcome is the immediate cessation of the system.'
    }
