        content: '<div class="doc-section"><p><strong>From:</strong> Data Privacy Officer<br><strong>To:</strong> VP of Commercial Strategy, VitaMatch<br><strong>Subject:</strong> Risk Flag - CLI Profiling</p><hr><p>I am deeply concerned about the "Cognitive Load Index." While we aren\'t asking users if they have a disability, the telemetry we are tracking (reading speed, repetition) effectively acts as a proxy for cognitive impairments. Under the AI Act, exploiting vulnerabilities related to disability is prohibited. We are steering them toward more expensive, worse plans.</p><hr><p><strong>From:</strong> VP of Commercial Strategy<br><strong>To:</strong> Data Privacy Officer<br><strong>Subject:</strong> RE: Risk Flag - CLI Profiling</p><p>We do not collect medical data. We do not ask for diagnoses. We are evaluating website navigation skills, not medical conditions. If someone is bad at using a website, we give them a simpler website. It is UX optimization, not a disability issue. We are fully compliant.</p></div>'
