              text: 'Your Honour, it is very offensive to have a computer try to guess someone\'s religion or race just to sell them things. This violates the general spirit of the AI Act, which says that AI should be human-centric and respect our values. Aura Analytics is using technology to create divisions in society by putting people into boxes based on how they look. We should ban this system because it is a violation of our privacy and it makes people feel like they are being judged by a machine in public.',
              judge_response: 'The court shares your concern about societal division, but I need you to address the specific statutory text. Under which Article and legal test do you claim this system is prohibited?',
              legal_reasoning: 'Correct in direction but lacks any reference to Art 5(1)(g) or the specific legal test of "inferring protected characteristics from biometric data."'
