              text: 'Your Honour, the respondent\'s comparison is legally baseless. The exception in Article 5(1)(g) for labelling or filtering is explicitly restricted to lawfully acquired biometric datasets in the area of law enforcement, migration, or asylum. It does not provide a general license for private firms to biometrically profile the public for profit. Aura Analytics is not a law enforcement agency, and they are not filtering a pre-existing lawful dataset; they are performing real-time inference of protected characteristics on the general public, which is exactly the activity the Article prohibits.',
              judge_response: 'The text of the exception is indeed very narrow. Dr. Sterling, does Aura Analytics claim to be a law enforcement or migration authority? If not, how do you qualify for this exception?',
