              judge_response: 'Counsel, there is no \"low-resolution\" exception or \"safe-harbor\" for 64-point facial maps in the AI Act. The prohibition applies to *any* biometric categorisation for these purposes, regardless of resolution.',
              legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It invents a "low-resolution" exception and a "safe-harbor" rule that do not exist in the AI Act.'
