              id: 'arg3-plausible',
              quality: 'plausible',
              text: 'Your Honour, the probabilistic nature of the system means it should be regulated under the \"Bias and Non-Discrimination\" rules of Article 10(2). Because the system only provides an estimation, the harm is not the categorisation itself, but the risk that the algorithm might be biased against certain ethnicities. Aura Analytics should be allowed to continue using Prism-AI provided they conduct a mandatory bias audit and prove that their probability scores are equally accurate for all racial and religious groups. This ensures the \"inference\" is technically sound and non-discriminatory.',
              judge_response: 'Counsel, you are suggesting that a prohibited practice is acceptable if it is \"unbiased.\" But if Article 5 bans the *purpose* of inferring race, does it matter how accurate or fair the inference is?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It suggests that "unbiased" prohibited practices are legal. But Art 5 prohibitions are absolute—the *purpose* of the system (inferring race/religion) is what is banned, not just its potential for bias.'
