              text: 'Your Honour, the use of a diagnostic tool that works differently based on skin color is a prohibited practice under Article 5(1)(c). This is a form of social scoring where the AI evaluates people differently based on their social characteristics, leading to detrimental treatment in a health context. Because the system discriminates against protected groups, it is an unacceptable risk to fundamental rights and should never have been classified as a high-risk system. It must be permanently banned as a prohibited practice under the general safety framework of the Act.',
              judge_response: 'Counsel, Article 5(1)(c) refers to social scoring by public authorities or on their behalf. This is a medical diagnostic tool. Are you not confusing high-risk non-compliance with the absolute prohibitions?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This satisfies the user\'s requirement for the wrong option. It misclassifies a high-risk system failure as a prohibited practice, confusing the Art. 10 data requirements with the Art. 5 social scoring ban.'
