              judge_response: 'Accuracy is indeed required by Article 15, but is the 74% sensitivity a failure of accuracy, or a failure of the risk management system to address a specific bias? Which article provides the more precise remedy for this failure?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is a plausible error. Art. 15 does require accuracy, but in the context of bias, Art. 9 (Risk Management) and Art. 10 (Data) are the primary statutory tools. Accuracy is the *result* of good data and risk management. This tests whether the student understands the architecture of the Act.'
