              text: 'Your Honour, the respondent\'s \"utilitarian\" defense is a direct violation of the fundamental rights principles that underpin the AI Act. While Article 9(4) mentions a benefit-risk balance, that balance does not permit a provider to knowingly accept a significantly higher risk for a specific protected subgroup, such as darker-skinned patients (Evidence 6). Article 10(3) specifically mandates that datasets address possible biases to ensure non-discrimination. A system that achieves \'aggregate\' accuracy by failing a minority demographic is not a compliant high-risk system; it is a defective product that fails to meet the safety and fundamental rights standards required for deployment in the Union.',
              judge_response: 'The court agrees. Aggregate metrics cannot hide systemic bias against a protected group. The \'benefit\' of a system must be evaluated across the entire intended population.',
