        date: 'March 12, 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Admission Log: Patient #8821 (Marco Rossi)</div><p><strong>Time of Intake:</strong> 18:14 CET<br><strong>Presenting Symptoms:</strong> Acute substernal discomfort radiating to left arm, significant diaphoresis (sweating), mild shortness of breath.</p><p><strong>Triage Assessment:</strong><br>Initial vitals captured via automated intake kiosk. Data routed to TriageFlow AI.<br><div class="doc-highlight">TriageFlow AI Score: 2 (Green/Routine).</div><br>Estimated Safe Wait Time: 4-6 hours.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Clinical Notes & Outcome</div><p><strong>Attending:</strong> Dr. Julian Aris<br>Note: Dr. Aris visually reviewed the intake file at 18:22 CET. He noted the classic presentation of cardiac ischemia but did not upgrade the triage status in the system, leaving the AI\'s "Green" score active.</p><p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Patient was instructed to return to the general waiting room. At 22:19 CET (245 minutes post-intake), the patient collapsed in the waiting area. Resuscitation efforts were unsuccessful. Cause of death: Massive myocardial infarction.</p></div>'
