        date: 'April 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Email Thread: Post-Deployment Metrics</div><p><strong>From:</strong> Hospital Admin (St. Jude\'s ER Director)<br><strong>To:</strong> MediLogic Customer Success Team<br><strong>Date:</strong> April 15, 2025 10:22</p><p>MediLogic Team, the Q1 metrics are in. We are seeing a 98% adherence rate to the TriageFlow AI scores across all shifts. This is fantastic for our average wait-time metrics and department throughput.</p><p>We did have some pushback from the senior attending physicians. They complained heavily about the "mandatory essay" required to change a score when they disagree with the machine, calling it dangerous in a fast-paced ER. We told them <div class="doc-highlight">the AI is there to set the standard.</div> If they want to disagree with the algorithm, they should be prepared to defend it in writing to the board. The friction is working exactly as intended to keep them in line with the software.</p></div>'
