              judge_response: 'Transparency is certainly an issue, but does a better manual fix a system that is fundamentally designed to be difficult to override? Is the design itself not the primary violation here?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. While transparency (Art. 13) is relevant, the primary failure here is the *design* of the oversight mechanism (Art. 14). Better instructions won\'t fix a UI that is built to block human intervention.'
