              judge_response: 'Is the problem the system\'s accuracy, or the way the human is encouraged to interact with it? If a system is 100% accurate but prevents a doctor from acting on a rare exception, is it still compliant with the oversight rules?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is a plausible error. Art. 15 (Accuracy) is a separate requirement from Art. 14 (Oversight). A system could be very accurate but still violate Art. 14 if it makes human intervention too difficult. This tests the student\'s ability to isolate the oversight failure.'
