              text: 'Your Honour, you can\'t just say that Malik\'s rights are less important than \"preventing cheating.\" That isn\'t how the law works. The email shows the school knew the AI wasn\'t perfect for everyone but they used it anyway. That is a clear case of negligence. The AI Act says that high-risk systems should be safe for everyone, not just for people who look a certain way or act a certain way. The school should have waited until the AI was better before they forced everyone to use it.',
              judge_response: 'I hear your concern about negligence, but please ground this in the specific requirements of the risk management hierarchy in Article 9. How did they fail to mitigate the risk?',
              legal_reasoning: 'Correct in spirit but lacks statutory precision. It identifies "negligence" but fails to cite Art 9 or explain the risk management hierarchy.'
