      title: 'FleetLogistics Employee Handbook',
      date: 'March 2025',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">FleetLogistics Global Employee Handbook (2025 Edition)</div><p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 1, 2025</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Section 4: Acceptable Use and Network Monitoring</div><p>4.1 All computers, mobile devices, and network infrastructure provided by FleetLogistics remain the sole property of the company.</p><p>4.2 To protect proprietary information, defend against cyber threats, and ensure overall operational productivity, the company reserves the right to continuously monitor the use of company-issued equipment and networks.</p><p>4.3 <div class="doc-highlight">Data collected during this monitoring may include websites visited, time spent on specific tasks, active network usage, and email metadata.</div> Employees should have no expectation of privacy when utilizing corporate hardware.</p><p><em>*Note: A thorough review of the entire 112-page handbook reveals no specific mention of "PromoteOptima," algorithmic performance scoring, or the collection and categorization of biometric behavioral data (e.g., keystroke dynamics) for the purposes of career advancement or disciplinary action.</em></p></div>'
