            judge_response: 'Transparency is a key pillar, but does a disclosure fix a system that is fundamentally biased in its design? If the dataset itself is non-compliant under Article 10, does \"telling people\" make it lawful?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It identifies a transparency issue (Art. 13), but for this scenario, the core violation is Art. 10 (data governance). A disclosure notice doesn\'t fix the underlying discriminatory data. This tests if the student can prioritize the substantive failure over the procedural one.'
