            judge_response: 'Counsel, Article 5(1)(e) refers to untargeted scraping of *facial images* for recognition databases. It does not ban the use of lawful police records for risk assessment. You are citing the wrong prohibition.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It misapplies a biometric scraping prohibition (Art 5.1e) to a data governance case involving criminal records, showing a basic misunderstanding of the Act\'s categories.'
