            quality: 'weak',
            text: 'Your Honour, the computer is just repeating its own mistakes. The internal email says it\'s a self-reinforcing loop, which means the more the computer discriminates, the more it thinks it\'s right. This is exactly what the AI Act was supposed to stop: machines making up their own reality. Article 15 says you have to be accurate, but 92% accuracy doesn\'t mean anything if the computer is just agreeing with itself. The Justice Department should have turned off the self-learning feature as soon as they saw the problem.',
