            judge_response: 'Counsel, the AI Act is a Regulation with direct effect and its rules on high-risk accuracy are mandatory, not optional. And a "right to appeal" does not excuse the deployment of a fundamentally inaccurate system.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It applies the wrong framework (GDPR) and wrongly claims the AI Act is optional for judicial bodies, which are explicitly included in Annex III.'
