      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Sworn Statement to the Judicial Conduct Authority</div><p><strong>Witness:</strong> Hon. Judge Sarah Vane, Circuit Court Magistrate</p><p>"The Ministry calls it a \'support tool,\' but it\'s a ghost in the courtroom dictating our every move. We are told by the Ministry that we are legally in charge, but the software is designed to make you feel like you\'re failing if you disagree with it. The red flashing warnings, the lockout screens—it is psychological conditioning."</p><p>"I had a case last month where a young mother shoplifted baby formula. The AI recommended three years because of her zip code\'s risk profile. I wanted to give her probation. But <div class="doc-highlight">the \'compliance score\' on my profile affects my promotion prospects</div> to the High Court. If I fill out the \'Reasoning Form,\' the prosecutor immediately appeals, and I get flagged by the Administrator. In a busy court where I see forty cases a day, it\'s just easier to follow the red numbers than to write a ten-page defense of your own legal intuition and face a disciplinary review."</p></div>'
