            judge_response: 'Counsel, while GDPR is relevant, we are litigating under the AI Act. And since a human judge *did* sign the order, the "solely automated" threshold of Article 22 is difficult to reach. Does the AI Act not provide a more specific remedy for high-risk systems?',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It applies the wrong framework (GDPR) and focuses on the \"solely automated\" test, which is easily bypassed by a human signature. The AI Act\'s Art 14 oversight requirements are much more stringent for high-risk systems.'
