            text: 'Your Honour, the respondent is conflating \"consistency\" with \"justice.\" Article 14(2) requires that human oversight measures minimize the risks that may emerge from the AI system itself\u2014most notably the risk of automation bias and the loss of human agency. The audit (Evidence 4) showing a 94% adherence rate proves the AI has not minimized risk, but has instead superseded human judgment. In Thomas Miller\'s case (Evidence 1), the AI failed to capture unique mitigating factors. True equality before the law requires the consideration of individual circumstances, which the \"effective\" human oversight of Article 14 is specifically designed to protect against algorithmic rigidity.',
            judge_response: 'The court agrees. If \"consistency\" is achieved by making the judge ignore the specific facts of a case, it is a failure of justice, not a victory for equality. Article 14 is there to ensure the human can still see what the AI misses.',
