          judge_response: 'Counsel, you are proposing a procedural fix. But does a fine for documentation help the 200,000 households who were in the dark? Is the lack of a physical fallback not a more direct violation of the safety rules in Article 15?',
          legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It suggests a procedural remedy (Art. 17 QMS, Art. 99 fines) instead of addressing the core safety violation (Art. 15). It focuses on \"administrative oversight\" rather than the lack of a redundant fallback mechanism.'
