      type: 'policy-document',
      title: 'StrategicPulse Risk Management Plan',
      date: 'February 2025',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">StrategicPulse Risk Management Protocol</div><p><strong>Project:</strong> Citizen-Sync (VoterFlow AI)<br><strong>Compliance Framework:</strong> Internal Commercial Standards</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Risk Assessment Matrix</div><table class="doc-table"><tr><th>Identified Risk Vector</th><th>Severity</th><th>Implemented Mitigation</th></tr><tr><td>Data Storage Leaks (PII)</td><td>High</td><td>End-to-end encryption, regular penetration testing.</td></tr><tr><td>Server Downtime / High Latency</td><td>Medium</td><td>Redundant cloud instances via AWS.</td></tr><tr><td>Unscheduled Algorithmic Hallucinations</td><td>Low</td><td>Keyword blocklists to prevent profanity.</td></tr></table></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Excluded Scope</div><p><div class="doc-highlight">Not Assessed: Impact on democratic integrity, societal polarization, or psychological manipulation of voters.</div></p><p><strong>Executive Rationale:</strong> The VoterFlow system is officially classified by StrategicPulse legal counsel as a "B2B Commercial Marketing Support Tool." Therefore, risks to broader electoral processes, voter autonomy, and fundamental democratic rights are considered strictly out of scope for our engineering risk management hierarchy. The system is designed to sell a political brand, identically to selling consumer goods.</p></div>'
