            judge_response: 'Counsel, you are making a sophisticated argument for high-risk compliance. However, even if it weren\'t high-risk, does Article 50(1) not create a more fundamental, standalone duty for all interactive AI? Is the lack of a simple label not the more direct breach here?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It misapplies the "High-Risk" framework (Art 13). While health AI *can* be high-risk, Art 50(1) is a universal transparency rule for interactive AI. Arguing for High-Risk registration avoids the simple fact that they broke a basic disclosure rule.'
