            judge_response: 'Counsel, while the mimicry is deceptive, does it meet the high threshold of a \"subliminal technique\" that the subject is unaware of? Or is it a failure to disclose AI origin? Are you not misapplying the prohibition categories?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is a trap. It misclassifies a transparency violation as a "Prohibited Practice." While manipulative, using AI to mimic a style is specifically addressed by the disclosure rules of Art 50, not the high-threshold "subliminal manipulation" ban.'
