      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Formal Notice of Non-Compliance</div><p><strong>Issued By:</strong> European AI Office, GPAI Enforcement Division<br><strong>Reference:</strong> GPAI-2025-089A<br><strong>Addressee:</strong> Aether AI Corp</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Regulatory Deficiencies</div><p>Following a preliminary review of the technical documentation submitted for the Aether-Lumina general-purpose AI model, the AI Office notes the critical absence of mandatory statutory requirements. Specifically, the provider has failed to supply:<br>1. Detailed information on the <div class="doc-highlight">computational resources used to train the model</div> (e.g., total FLOPs, exact hardware configuration), in direct violation of Art 53(1)(a) / Annex XI.<br>2. Known or estimated energy consumption metrics.<br>3. A sufficiently detailed summary of the training content utilizing the mandatory AI Office template.</p><p>Your blanket claim of absolute trade secret privilege is not consistent with the regulatory framework. Trade secret protection does not nullify mandatory safety disclosures. Rectify these omissions within 15 days to avoid severe financial penalties.</p></div>'
