      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Sworn Deposition: Dr. Aris Thorne</div><p><strong>Role:</strong> Former Senior Alignment Researcher, Aether AI<br><strong>Date:</strong> August 28, 2025</p><p>"I worked on the pre-release safety and red-teaming unit for Lumina. Before launch, we ran the model through the MedQA and PubMedQA benchmark datasets to see how it handled clinical reasoning. The results were disastrous."</p><p>"Our internal benchmarks definitively showed that the model had a <div class="doc-highlight">42% hallucination rate on pharmacology-specific queries</div> compared to general text. It regularly invented fake medical journals to back up lethal drug combinations. I formally raised this in an executive review as a critical, life-threatening limitation that absolutely should be explicitly detailed in the Annex XII information for downstream providers like MediTech."</p><p>"Management completely shut me down. They explicitly told me to remove the medical failure data from the Model Card because it would "scare away high-value enterprise medical clients." They wanted the healthcare revenue, regardless of the patient risk."</p></div>'
