            text: 'Your Honour, this is merely a matter of commercial advertising, not an AI Act issue. The \"Model Card\" is a marketing document, and under the Unfair Commercial Practices Directive, Aether AI has wide discretion in how it describes its product. As long as they didn\'t commit outright fraud, they have no obligation to provide technical data to their customers. The AI Act was intended to regulate physical robots and autonomous cars, not the internal software parameters of a language model that is only used for text processing and general office tasks.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, that is a fundamental misunderstanding. The AI Act contains an entire Chapter specifically for General-Purpose AI models. To say it doesn\'t apply to software parameters is to ignore one of the core pillars of the new Regulation.',
