            text: 'Your Honour, the respondent\'s claim that compute and energy are \"optional\" is flatly contradicted by the statutory text. Annex XI, point 2(d) and (e), explicitly lists the computational resources used to train the model and the known or estimated energy consumption as mandatory elements of the technical documentation for all GPAI providers. These are not ESG suggestions; they are necessary data points for the AI Office to evaluate model capabilities and systemic risk. Aether AI\'s internal emails (Evidence 3) prove they knowingly withheld this data to protect commercial interests, constituting a direct violation of their Article 53(1)(a) disclosure duties.',
            judge_response: 'The law is explicit. Annex XI does not contain a \"proprietary hardware\" exception. If the Office requests the compute data as per the Annex, the provider must supply it. Why was the notice in Evidence 4 ignored?',
