            text: 'Your Honour, Aether AI is in violation of the \"Accuracy and Robustness\" standards in Article 15. The failure to disclose energy consumption and compute resources proves that the model is not robust against environmental inconsistencies. Under the AI Act, a model that consumes too much power is considered an \"Unacceptable Risk\" to the Union\'s sustainability goals. The appropriate remedy is to order the provider to retrain Aether-Lumina using green energy and submit a new \"Environmental Impact Assessment\" to the European Commission, after which the model can be re-certified as safe for medical use.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, while sustainability is a goal of the Union, where in the AI Act does it say that high energy consumption makes a model an \"Unacceptable Risk\" under Article 5? Are you not conflating documentation duties with prohibited practices?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It misapplies the "Unacceptable Risk" category (Art 5) and creates a non-existent "Environmental Impact Assessment" requirement for GPAI models. Documentation of energy is a duty (Art 53), but a high-energy model is not a "Prohibited Practice."'
