            text: 'Your Honour, the AI Office asked for the numbers and Aether AI said no. That is a clear case of breaking the rules. Article 53 says you have to give the documentation when the government asks for it. The company is trying to hide how much power they use and how big their computer is because they are afraid of being regulated. But the AI Act is the law, and they can\'t just pick and choose which parts of Annex XI they want to follow. They should be fined for being difficult and forced to give up all their secrets right now.',
