    modelAnswer: 'LexiClone AI violated the EU AI Act on two primary counts as a GPAI provider. First, it failed Article 53(1)(d) by providing a summary that was too vague to enable rightsholders to enforce their interests (Evidence 4); a summary that omits 450 billion tokens from pirate libraries (Evidence 6) is not \"sufficiently detailed.\" Second, the provider breached Article 53(1)(c) by failing to put in place a policy to comply with Union copyright law. The scraper logs (Evidence 2) prove the firm used technology to bypass rather than identify reservations of rights, and the internal email (Evidence 3) proves this was a deliberate choice to prioritize performance over compliance. Transformative use and technical necessity do not grant an exemption from the mandatory transparency and opt-out duties of the AI Act.'
